docs.text: Visit Fente It technical documenation site . See the simple guide for creating a mkdocs and deploy the site here This readme site is generated when creating a MkDocs site. Welcome to MkDocs For full documentation visit mkdocs.org . Commands mkdocs new [dir-name] - Create a new project. mkdocs serve - Start the live-reloading docs server. mkdocs build - Build the documentation site. mkdocs -h - Print help message and exit. Project layout mkdocs.yml # The configuration file. docs/ index.md # The documentation homepage. ... # Other markdown pages, images and other files.

docs.text: Markdown tips MkDocs uses Jhon Gruber markdown . I think GitHub basix writing and formatting syntax is a better guideline. Some basic syntax: /** H1 **/ # /** H2 **/ ## /** H3 **/ ### /** Image **/ ![Text](path) /** Link **/ [Text](url) /** italic text **/ _italic_ /** bold text **/ *italic*
